cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DC 

The paper focuses on resource allocation in networks, specifically in elastic optical networks. This falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and robotics (cs.RO) as it involves configuring and managing resources in a network. The paper also discusses the use of different models for resource allocation, which could fall under information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control (cs.SI). Finally, the paper evaluates the overall network resource utilization, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
